buzzy
------------------------------------------
Buzzy is a package manager that isn't tied to one particular operating system
or distribution. It's useful for third-party software developers that would
like to provide native binary packages for the software that they write,
without having to maintain separate packaging scripts for a multitude of
operating systems, distributions, and versions.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.4.12-3
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libclogger2-1.0.0-1bl1
  libcork15-0.15.0-1bl1
  libyaml0_2-0.1.6-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.3.0-2
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2
  ninja-1.8.2-2
  python-2.7.14-1
  ragel-6.10-1bl1
  ruby-2.3.6-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/dcreager/buzzy

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/dcreager/buzzy/archive/0.6.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack buzzy-0.6.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./buzzy-0.6.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/buzzy-0.6.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/buzzy-0.6.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(buzzy)
  /usr/bin/buzzy.exe
  /usr/bin/buzzydock
  /usr/share/buzzy/config.yaml
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/buzzy.README
  /usr/share/doc/buzzy/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/buzzy/README.md

